[Result "*"]

1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 d6 3. c3 Nf6 4. Bd3 Bg4
{ Applying pressure to white's position and making white's plan of d4  (after Bc2)  harder }
5. Bc2 Nc6 6. d4 cxd4 7. cxd4 Bxf3 8. gxf3
{ If instead 8. Qxf3 Nxd4 wins a pawn } 8... e5
{ Black strikes black in the center. d5 is also a possibility } 9. dxe5 dxe5
10. Nc3 Bc5
{ Black has a slightly better position with smooth development and good piece activity. }
*

[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "Sicilian: 2.Nf3 d6 Moves that aren't 3.d4"]
[Black " Sicilian: 2.Nf3 d6 3.c3 Nf6 4.Bd3 Delayed alapin: Kopec System"]
[Result "*"]

1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 d6 3. c3 Nf6 4. Bd3 Bg4
{ Applying pressure to white's position and making white's plan of d4  (after Bc2)  harder }
5. Bc2 Nc6 6. d4 cxd4 7. cxd4 Bxf3 8. gxf3
{ If instead 8. Qxf3 Nxd4 wins a pawn } 8... e5
{ Black strikes black in the center. d5 is also a possibility } 9. d5 Nd4
{ Black's knight on d4 is strong, attacks the weak f3, and if needed can break up white's bishop pair with ...Nxc2  (White can prevent this, but it takes some defensive moves and black can develop in the meantime)  . One possible plan for black is to improve Bf8 by getting it out of the pawn chain  (Be7 O-O Qd7 Bd8 Bb6 is an example)  and can also aim for pressure on the c file. }
*

[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
