[White "Sicilian: 2.Nf3 d6 Moves that aren't 3.d4"]
[Black " Sicilian: 2.Nf3 d6 3.c3 Nf6 4.Bd3 Delayed alapin: Kopec System"]
[Result "*"]

1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 d6 3. c3 Nf6 4. Bd3 Bg4
{ Applying pressure to white's position and making white's plan of d4  (after Bc2)  harder }
5. Bc2 Nc6 6. d3
{ White employs a slow but solid plan of development. White waits on d4 until he is better developed. }
6... g6
{ The long diagonal is a strong place for the bishop and is ideally placed on g7 }
7. Nbd2 Bg7 8. h3 { Forcing black to decide what to do with his bishop } 8...
Bd7
{ Black temporarily prevented d4, the bishop's job on g4 is done. There is no need to take on f3 which not only gives up the bishop pair, but also helps white free up his position with Nxf3. }
9. O-O O-O 10. d4 { This seems strong but is premature. } 10... cxd4 11. Nxd4
Nxd4 12. cxd4 Rc8
{ Even though white has 2 pawns in the center, black has active play with ideas of Qc7/Qb8 and maybe queenside expansion. White can't really do much with his pawn center, and it can become a target. }
*

