1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 d6 3. c3 Nf6 4. h3
{ White is looking for an improved version of the Kopec System  (Bd3-Bc2 with ideas of d4 with a Ruy-Lopez type position)  . After White plays Bd3, we cannot play ...Bg4. }
4... Nbd7 5. Bd3 b6
{ Black is trying to solidify his position with ...b6 and also helps Black develop his bishop to ...b7 where the bishop will increase the pressure on e4. }
6. O-O Bb7
{ Black's idea to develop all his queenside pieces before castling so he can go for a control of the queenside. }
7. Re1 Qc7 8. Bc2 Rc8
{ Black wants to exploit the placement of the bishop on c2. Now d4 is not possible for White because of the X-Ray attack along the c file. }
