{ After the ...d5 break Black will obtain a great position. } 12. exd5
{ It looks like White can take advantage of Black's king but after ...Nxd5, White doesn't really have anything to do. }
12... Nxd5
{ Black has the superior position. White has an isolated pawn on d4 which Black can put more pressure on in the future. Black can also develop soundly with ...Be7 and then ...O-O. Apart from all of this, Black also has the decisive threat of ...Bxa3 followed by ...Qxc2 that white has to deal with. }
