9... e6 10. b3
{ White wants to develop his pieces on the queenside first before an immediate action in the center. }
10... Be7 11. Bb2 { The bishop on b2 supports d4 indirectly. } 11... O-O 12.
Rc1
{ White's idea with Rc2 to have an X Ray against the Black queen. If Black isn't careful, White can open up the c file with d4, cxd4 and cxd4. }
12... Qb8 { Moving the queen out of the way. } 13. d4
{ White's pieces are finally developed so he goes for d4. } 13... cxd4 14. cxd4
d5 15. e5 Ne4
{ This position is very good for Black. Black has control of the c file, Black's knight on ...e4 is very strong and Black also has ideas of ...f6 to undermine White's center. }
*

