[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "Sicilian: 2.Nf3 d6 Moves that aren't 3.d4"]
[Black "Sicilian: 2.Nf3 d6 3.Bb5+ Bd7 "]
[Result "*"]

1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 d6 3. Bb5+ Bd7
{ Black blocks with the bishop so he could have smooth development. Nc6/Nd7 are also playable. }
4. Bxd7+ Qxd7
{ 3. Bb5+ has helped black develop  (trades the bishops but develops black's queen)  but Bc8 was black's good bishop. Black can play Nc6 with Nf6 and g6 Bg7  (e6 Be7 is an alternative, which one is used depends on what white plays)  and O-O with easy play. }
5. c4 { Aiming for d4 with a maroczy bind position } 5... Nc6
{ Even though black can't play d6-d5 yet black has fast development. Black can restrain d5 with e5 but it seems like white is better there  (though it is an interesting alternative if you want to avoid playing the Maroczy bind as black)  . }
6. d4 cxd4 7. Nxd4 g6 { Developing the bishop on the long diagonal } 8. Nc3 Bg7
9. Be3
{ White has more space and active pieces but black has fast development and counterplay }
9... Nf6 10. f3 { Or else black could play Ng4 } 10... O-O
{ Black has ideas like Rfc8 with Qd8 and Nd7-c5. Black could also play for either b5 with a6 or expand on the queenside with a5-a4 etc }
*

