10... Ne4 11. Nbd2 Nxd2 12. Bxd2 Be7 13. Rc1 O-O
{ White has a strong center but black can attack it with f6 and also can control the c file. Black also has a good bishop with most of blacks pawns on the opposite color as it, unlike whites bishop. The position is equal. }
