[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "Sicilian: 2.Nf3 d6 Moves that aren't 3.d4"]
[Black "1.e4 c5 2.Nf3 d6 3.b4: Delayed Wing Gambit"]
[Result "*"]

1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 d6 3. b4
{ Offering a pawn for development and center control. } 3... Nf6
{ It is more dangerous to accept the gambit here than in 2.b4 as black often had the idea of ...d5 and here this would take 2 moves rather than one. Black is playing for quick development. }
4. bxc5 Nxe4 5. cxd6 Nc6 { Black develops, he is the one offering a gambit. }
6. Bb5
{ 6.dxe7 Bxe7   or even  6...Qxe7  would offer black more than enough compensation with his enormous lead in development. }
6... e6 { Black intends to take on d6 with the bishop, then castle kingside. }
7. d3 { Forcing matters. 7.0-0 Bxd6 is about equal. } 7... Nxd6
{ Forcing the bishop to retreat or lose the bishop pair. } 8. Bxc6+ bxc6
{ Black has a worse pawn structure but has a lead in development and the bishop pair. Black is no worse and can easily develop with Be7, 0-0, Qc7. He also can sometimes use one or more of the following ideas: c5 with Bb7, Ba6, Nf5. }
*

