[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "Sicilian: 2.Nc3"]
[Black "Sicilian: 2.Nc3 a6 3.g3 main line with 6.Nge2"]
[Result "*"]

1. e4 c5 2. Nc3 a6 { Black prepares ...b5 which gains queenside space. } 3. g3
b5 4. Bg2 Bb7 5. d3
{ White usually wants to play d3 as it is useful for development and it supports the e4 pawn. }
5... e6
{ Black's position is very flexible. He can play ...d5 or ...d6 combined with ...Nf6 and ...Be7  (or ...Bd6 if black plays ...d5)  . }
6. Nge2 Nf6
{ Black should not commit his d pawn yet, it could go to either d5 or d6. } 7.
O-O d6
{ With Bg2 unblocked and exerting pressure on the center, d6 seems more natural than d5 as the d5 pawn could come under pressure. The position is closed, white has no major threats. Black can finish his development with ...Nc6 ...Be7 and ...O-O with a good position. }
*

[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "Sicilian: 2.Nc3"]
[Black "Sicilian: 2.Nc3 a6 3.g3 main line with 6.Nh3"]
[Result "*"]

1. e4 c5 2. Nc3 a6 { Black prepares ...b5 which gains queenside space. } 3. g3
b5 4. Bg2 Bb7 5. d3
{ White usually wants to play d3 as it is useful for development and it supports the e4 pawn. }
5... e6
{ Black's position is very flexible. He can play ...d5 or ...d6 combined with ...Nf6 and ...Be7  (or ...Bd6 if black plays ...d5)  . }
6. Nh3
{ It might seem awkward to put the knight on the rim, but at least it doesn't block Bg2. }
6... Nf6
{ b4 7. Ne2 d5 is also strong and scores well for black in master games. 7. e5 is not good here because Bg2 would be hanging. }
7. O-O d6
{ d5 is not as strong here because the center can come under heavy pressure as Nh3 doesn't block Bg2. If black plays ...d5, some of white's ideas include: Re1+/Bg5/Nf4. }
8. f4 Nc6 { Preventing e5. Qc7 is also playable. } 9. f5
{ If White instead just develops, Black can do the same. } 9... exf5 10. exf5
Be7 11. Nf4 O-O
{ The position is complex, but black is doing fine. He is ahead on developent. White has the d5 square, but black has the e5 outpost to counter it. }
*

