[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "Sicilian: 2.Nc3"]
[Black "Sicilian: 2.Nc3 a6 3.g3 main line with 5.Nge2 and 6.d4"]
[Result "*"]

1. e4 c5 2. Nc3 a6 { Black prepares ...b5 which gains queenside space. } 3. g3
b5 4. Bg2 Bb7 5. Nge2
{ White aims to transpose into the open Sicilian with d4. } 5... e6 6. d4 cxd4
7. Nxd4
{ White has transposed into the Kan, but the g3 lines aren't the most dangerous. Even so, Black should know what to do. }
7... Nf6 8. O-O
{ 8.a3  d6  allows Black to get a satisfactory Scheveningen structure, he can develop his pieces with  ...Be7  ,  ...0-0  ,  ...Qc7  and  ...Nbd7.  One thing to watch out for is that  ...Qc7  should be played before  ...Be7  because Black will have defended his b7-bishop, neutralizing the  e5  discovered attack. }
8... b4
{ The most ambitious. Black aims to win the e4-pawn. White could have prevented ...b4 by playing a3, but that would lose a tempo and Black would be able to get a good position with normal development. }
9. Na4 Bxe4
{ 9...Nxe4?  10.Re1  Black is under a lot of pressure and  Ne4  is pinned to  Bb7. }
10. Bxe4 Nxe4
{ White has a lead in development, but Black has an extra pawn and a 2 vs. 0 central pawn majority. If Black defends against White's attack without White forcing a concession, his extra pawn and center should be the most important features of the position. }
11. Re1 { White gains a tempo and creates an x-ray on Ke8. } 11... Nc5 12. c3
{ White aims to open the queenside.   12.Qf3  Ra7  doesn't change much. Black can develop his rook through the 7th rank after he plays  ...d5. }
12... Nxa4 13. Qxa4 bxc3 { Black isolates White's pawn. } 14. bxc3
{ Most dangerous seems to be  14.Nxe6!  Best play seems to be  14...fxe6  15.Rxe6+  Be7  16.Bg5  Nc6  17.Bxe7  Nxe7  18.Rae1  O-O  19.Rxe7  Qb6  20.R7e2  cxb2  21.Rb1  Qb5  22.Qxb5  axb5  23.Rexb2  with a drawn rook endgame. I didn't realize this when I recommended  13...bxc3. If you would like to avoid these complications,13...Be7  is a safer alternative. }
14... Be7 { Black has survived the attack and can castle next. } *

