[Result "*"]

1. e4 c5 2. d4 cxd4 3. c3
{ Qxd4 Nc6 gives black a development advantage, while Nf3 d6 transposes into the open sicilian. }
3... Nf6 4. Bd3 dxc3
{ Black gets a superior smith morra gambit as Bd3 is misplaced  (it would rather be on c4)  . Nc6 or e5 should also be enough for an advantage. }
5. Nxc3 e5 { d6 or Nc6 are also fine. } 6. Nf3 Nc6 7. O-O d6
{ Black's position is better, white has insufficient compensation for the pawn. For example: }
8. Qe2 Be7 9. Be3 O-O 10. Rfd1 Be6
{ This seems like a satisfactory Najdorf position without white's c pawn and without a6. Black can improve his position by playing Rc8 with a6 and b5. }
