{ If white plays to castle kingside, the f3 move is out of place. Black could play it like a Najdorf with moves like 0-0 Be6 and d5  (a5-a4 is also an idea. If white plays a4 to prevent black from playing a4 black can play Nb4 without worrying about a3 pushing the knight back.) }
8... O-O
{ This is very much like a Najdorf, but black has not committed to a6 yet. Since my current recommendation in the English attack is to play 10...a6-a5, the extra tempo could come in handy as black can play a5 in one move. }
9. Qd2 Be6 10. O-O-O a5
{ Black gets a superior Najdorf English attack 10...a5 as he got the move Nc6 in for free. }
