[Result "*"]

1. e4 c5 2. b4
{ White is giving up a pawn in order to deflect the c5 pawn from controlling the center and to open lines }
2... cxb4 3. d4 d5
{ Striking back in the center. The b4 pawn stops Nc3 and so the black queen can't be immediately pushed off if white takes. }
4. exd5 Nf6
{ Though ...Qxd5 is playable and Nc3 can't push off the queen yet, white has ideas of c4 which gains space and forces either the retreat of the queen or bxc3  (which allows Nxc3)  . Nf6 prepares to take on d5 with the knight instead. }
5. a3 Nxd5 6. axb4 e5
{ Black attacks d4 and b4 and is currently better developed. Blacks position is better. }
*

