[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "Sicilian: Other sidelines for white"]
[Black "Sicilian: 2.Bc4"]
[Result "*"]

1. e4 c5 2. Bc4 { White commits his bishop too soon. } 2... e6
{ Black can block the diagonal and play against Bc4. Black also sometimes can play ...d5 with tempo. }
3. Nc3 { Developing and preventing ...d5 for now. } 3... a6 4. Nf3
{ Allowing b5, though white quickly developing. } 4... Nf6 5. e5 d5 6. exd6 b5
{ As the bishop is great on b7, this is a helpful in between move. b5 also gains space on the queenside. }
7. Be2 Bxd6
{ Black's position is better. He has lots of space on the queenside and no real trouble developing. After Bb7 black's bishops pressure white's kingside. }
*

